1. Configure network access to pfSense and enable SSH (System ➜ Advanced ➜ Enable Secure Shell).
2. Via the web interface http://host check for updates and install critical patches if available.
3. Copy the contents of the current `pfSense` directory to the remote host root:
   ```sh
   scp -r ./etc root@host:/etc
   ```
4. Connect to the remote host as `root` and install the required packages (editor `vim` optional):
   ```sh
   ssh user@host
   pkg install -y xmlstarlet
   pkg install -y vim
   set PKG = `pkg search -x frr | awk '/pfSense/{print $1}'`
   echo y | pkg install "$PKG"
   ```
5. Clear logs and backups:
   ```sh
   ssh user@host "find /var/log -type f -exec rm -f {} +"
   ssh user@host "rm -f /cf/conf/backup/*"
   ```
6. Reboot pfSense to start the new initialization cycle:
   ```sh
   ssh user@host 'reboot'
   ```
